ingredients: Spaghetti, Eggs, Pancetta, Pecorino Romano cheese, Black pepper
cooking_instructions: 1. Cook spaghetti in salted water until al dente. 2. Fry pancetta until crisp. 3. Whisk eggs and cheese. 4. Drain pasta, mix with pancetta, then quickly stir in egg mixture. 5. Season with black pepper and serve.

ingredients: Chicken breast, Yogurt, Lemon juice, Garam masala, Tomato puree, Cream, Onion, Garlic, Ginger
cooking_instructions: 1. Marinate chicken in yogurt and spices. 2. Grill chicken until charred. 3. Sauté onion, garlic, and ginger. 4. Add tomato puree and cream. 5. Simmer with grilled chicken. Serve with rice.

ingredients: Ripe bananas, Almond milk, Vegetable oil, Brown sugar, Flour, Baking soda, Cinnamon
cooking_instructions: 1. Mash bananas and mix with wet ingredients. 2. Combine dry ingredients separately. 3. Mix wet and dry ingredients. 4. Pour into loaf pan. 5. Bake at 350°F for 60 minutes.

ingredients: Beef chuck, Bacon, Red wine, Beef broth, Carrots, Onions, Mushrooms, Thyme
cooking_instructions: 1. Brown bacon and beef. 2. Add vegetables and sauté. 3. Add wine and broth, simmer for 2-3 hours. 4. Sauté mushrooms separately. 5. Combine and serve.

ingredients: Dashi stock, Miso paste, Tofu, Wakame seaweed, Green onions
cooking_instructions: 1. Heat dashi stock. 2. Dissolve miso paste in stock. 3. Add tofu and wakame. 4. Simmer gently. 5. Garnish with green onions.

ingredients: Tomatoes, Cucumbers, Red onion, Feta cheese, Kalamata olives, Olive oil, Oregano
cooking_instructions: 1. Chop tomatoes and cucumbers into chunks. 2. Slice red onion thinly. 3. Combine vegetables in a bowl. 4. Add crumbled feta and olives. 5. Drizzle with olive oil and sprinkle with oregano. 6. Toss gently and serve.

ingredients: Short-grain rice, Chicken thighs, Chorizo, Shrimp, Mussels, Bell peppers, Peas, Saffron, Garlic, Tomatoes, Chicken broth
cooking_instructions: 1. Brown chicken and chorizo in a paella pan. 2. Add rice, garlic, and saffron, stirring to coat. 3. Pour in broth and simmer. 4. Add vegetables and seafood. 5. Cook until rice is tender and a crust forms on the bottom. 6. Let rest before serving.

ingredients: Beef bones, Rice noodles, Beef sirloin, Bean sprouts, Thai basil, Lime, Hoisin sauce, Sriracha, Star anise, Cinnamon, Ginger
cooking_instructions: 1. Simmer beef bones with spices to make broth (6-8 hours). 2. Cook rice noodles. 3. Slice raw beef thinly. 4. Assemble bowls with noodles and beef. 5. Pour hot broth over to cook beef. 6. Serve with garnishes.

ingredients: Eggs, Tomatoes, Bell peppers, Onions, Garlic, Cumin, Paprika, Cayenne pepper, Olive oil
cooking_instructions: 1. Sauté onions and peppers until soft. 2. Add garlic and spices, then tomatoes. Simmer. 3. Make wells in the sauce and crack eggs into them. 4. Cover and cook until eggs are set. 5. Serve with bread.

ingredients: Flour, Butter, Brown sugar, White sugar, Eggs, Vanilla extract, Baking soda, Salt, Chocolate chips
cooking_instructions: 1. Cream butter and sugars. 2. Beat in eggs and vanilla. 3. Mix in dry ingredients. 4. Fold in chocolate chips. 5. Drop spoonfuls onto baking sheet. 6. Bake at 375°F for 9-11 minutes.

ingredients: Sushi rice, Nori sheets, Avocado, Cucumber, Imitation crab, Rice vinegar, Wasabi, Soy sauce
cooking_instructions: 1. Prepare sushi rice with vinegar. 2. Place nori on bamboo mat. 3. Spread rice on nori. 4. Add fillings. 5. Roll tightly. 6. Slice into pieces. 7. Serve with wasabi and soy sauce.

ingredients: Avocados, Lime juice, Red onion, Tomatoes, Cilantro, Jalapeño, Salt
cooking_instructions: 1. Mash avocados. 2. Finely chop onion, tomatoes, cilantro, and jalapeño. 3. Mix all ingredients. 4. Season with lime juice and salt. 5. Serve with tortilla chips.

ingredients: Beef tenderloin, Puff pastry, Mushrooms, Prosciutto, Dijon mustard, Egg (for egg wash)
cooking_instructions: 1. Sear beef. Brush with mustard. 2. Sauté and cool mushrooms. 3. Wrap beef in mushrooms and prosciutto. 4. Wrap in puff pastry. 5. Brush with egg wash. 6. Bake until golden and beef is cooked to desired doneness.

ingredients: Rice noodles, Shrimp, Tofu, Eggs, Bean sprouts, Peanuts, Lime, Fish sauce, Tamarind paste, Palm sugar
cooking_instructions: 1. Soak noodles. 2. Stir-fry shrimp and tofu. 3. Add beaten eggs. 4. Add noodles and sauce (made from fish sauce, tamarind, and sugar). 5. Toss with bean sprouts and peanuts. 6. Serve with lime wedges.

ingredients: Eggplant, Zucchini, Bell peppers, Tomatoes, Onions, Garlic, Herbs de Provence, Olive oil
cooking_instructions: 1. Slice vegetables. 2. Sauté onions and garlic. 3. Layer vegetables in a baking dish. 4. Drizzle with olive oil and sprinkle with herbs. 5. Bake until vegetables are tender.

ingredients: Veal cutlets, Flour, Eggs, Breadcrumbs, Lemon, Parsley, Vegetable oil
cooking_instructions: 1. Pound veal thin. 2. Dredge in flour, dip in beaten eggs, then coat with breadcrumbs. 3. Fry in oil until golden brown. 4. Serve with lemon wedges and parsley.

ingredients: Napa cabbage, Gochugaru (Korean red pepper flakes), Garlic, Ginger, Green onions, Fish sauce, Salt
cooking_instructions: 1. Salt cabbage and let sit for 2 hours. 2. Rinse and drain cabbage. 3. Mix other ingredients to make paste. 4. Coat cabbage with paste. 5. Ferment at room temperature for 1-5 days.

ingredients: Dried chickpeas, Onion, Garlic, Parsley, Cilantro, Cumin, Coriander, Baking powder, Oil for frying
cooking_instructions: 1. Soak chickpeas overnight. 2. Grind chickpeas with herbs and spices. 3. Form into balls. 4. Deep fry until golden and crispy. 5. Serve in pita with tahini sauce.

ingredients: Ladyfingers, Espresso, Mascarpone cheese, Eggs, Sugar, Cocoa powder
cooking_instructions: 1. Brew espresso and cool. 2. Beat egg yolks with sugar, add mascarpone. 3. Whip egg whites, fold into mixture. 4. Dip ladyfingers in espresso, layer with cream mixture. 5. Dust with cocoa powder. 6. Chill before serving.

ingredients: Shrimp, Lemongrass, Kaffir lime leaves, Galangal, Mushrooms, Tomatoes, Lime juice, Fish sauce, Chili paste
cooking_instructions: 1. Simmer lemongrass, lime leaves, and galangal in water. 2. Add mushrooms and tomatoes. 3. Add shrimp and cook briefly. 4. Season with lime juice, fish sauce, and chili paste. 5. Serve hot.

ingredients: Whole duck, Hoisin sauce, Scallions, Cucumber, Thin pancakes
cooking_instructions: 1. Clean and dry duck. 2. Hang to dry for 24 hours. 3. Roast duck in oven, basting regularly. 4. Carve meat and crispy skin. 5. Serve with pancakes, hoisin sauce, scallions, and cucumber.

ingredients: Açaí puree, Banana, Granola, Honey, Mixed berries
cooking_instructions: 1. Blend açaí puree with half a banana. 2. Pour into a bowl. 3. Top with sliced banana, granola, mixed berries. 4. Drizzle with honey.

ingredients: Lamb, Onions, Garlic, Tomatoes, Apricots, Almonds, Cinnamon, Cumin, Coriander, Couscous
cooking_instructions: 1. Brown lamb. 2. Add onions, garlic, spices. 3. Add tomatoes and apricots. 4. Simmer in tagine pot for 2 hours. 5. Toast almonds. 6. Serve over couscous, topped with almonds.

ingredients: Beets, Cabbage, Potatoes, Carrots, Onions, Beef broth, Sour cream, Dill
cooking_instructions: 1. Simmer beef in broth. 2. Add chopped vegetables. 3. Cook until tender. 4. Season with salt and pepper. 5. Serve with a dollop of sour cream and fresh dill.

ingredients: Teff flour, Chicken, Onions, Berbere spice, Eggs, Butter
cooking_instructions: 1. Ferment teff batter for injera. 2. Cook injera on a griddle. 3. Simmer chicken with onions and berbere. 4. Add boiled eggs to the stew. 5. Serve doro wat over injera.

ingredients: Sushi rice, Imitation crab, Cream cheese, Mayonnaise, Furikake, Nori sheets
cooking_instructions: 1. Mix crab, cream cheese, and mayonnaise. 2. Layer sushi rice in a baking dish. 3. Spread crab mixture on top. 4. Sprinkle with furikake. 5. Bake until hot. 6. Serve with nori sheets.

ingredients: Fresh mozzarella, Tomatoes, Fresh basil, Olive oil, Balsamic vinegar
cooking_instructions: 1. Slice mozzarella and tomatoes. 2. Arrange alternating slices on a plate. 3. Tuck basil leaves between slices. 4. Drizzle with olive oil and balsamic. 5. Season with salt and pepper.

ingredients: Chicken, Yogurt, Tomato sauce, Cream, Butter, Garam masala, Fenugreek leaves
cooking_instructions: 1. Marinate chicken in yogurt and spices. 2. Grill chicken. 3. Simmer tomato sauce with spices. 4. Add grilled chicken to sauce. 5. Finish with cream, butter, and fenugreek. Serve with naan.

ingredients: Beef bones, Rice noodles, Beef slices, Bean sprouts, Basil, Lime, Star anise, Cinnamon
cooking_instructions: 1. Simmer bones with spices for broth (6-8 hours). 2. Cook rice noodles. 3. Assemble bowls with noodles and raw beef slices. 4. Pour hot broth over. 5. Serve with bean sprouts, basil, and lime.

ingredients: Pie crust, Eggs, Heavy cream, Bacon, Gruyère cheese, Nutmeg
cooking_instructions: 1. Blind bake pie crust. 2. Cook bacon until crisp. 3. Whisk eggs with cream and nutmeg. 4. Layer bacon and cheese in crust. 5. Pour egg mixture over. 6. Bake until set and golden.

ingredients: Tomatoes, Cucumber, Bell pepper, Bread, Olive oil, Sherry vinegar, Garlic
cooking_instructions: 1. Soak bread in water. 2. Blend vegetables with soaked bread, oil, vinegar, and garlic. 3. Strain if desired. 4. Chill thoroughly. 5. Serve cold with chopped vegetable garnish.

ingredients: Beef strips, Mushrooms, Onions, Sour cream, Beef broth, Egg noodles, Paprika
cooking_instructions: 1. Sauté beef until browned. 2. Cook mushrooms and onions. 3. Add broth and simmer. 4. Stir in sour cream and paprika. 5. Serve over cooked egg noodles.

ingredients: Matcha powder, Heavy cream, Milk, Sugar, Egg yolks
cooking_instructions: 1. Whisk matcha with hot cream. 2. Beat egg yolks with sugar. 3. Combine mixtures and cook until thickened. 4. Chill thoroughly. 5. Churn in ice cream maker.

ingredients: Chicken thighs, Yogurt, Lemon juice, Garlic, Cumin, Cardamom, Pita bread
cooking_instructions: 1. Marinate chicken in yogurt and spices. 2. Grill or roast chicken. 3. Slice thinly. 4. Serve in pita with tahini sauce and vegetables.

ingredients: Flour, Eggs, Milk, Cheese (Emmentaler or Gruyère), Onions, Chives
cooking_instructions: 1. Make spätzle dough. 2. Push through spätzle maker into boiling water. 3. Layer cooked spätzle with cheese. 4. Top with caramelized onions and chives.

ingredients: White fish, Lime juice, Red onion, Cilantro, Chili peppers, Sweet potato, Corn
cooking_instructions: 1. Dice fish. 2. Marinate in lime juice for 30 minutes. 3. Mix with onion, cilantro, and chili. 4. Serve with sweet potato and corn.

ingredients: Beef chuck, Coconut milk, Lemongrass, Galangal, Turmeric leaves, Chili peppers
cooking_instructions: 1. Blend spices to a paste. 2. Simmer beef with spice paste and coconut milk. 3. Cook until liquid is absorbed and beef is tender. 4. Fry until dark and caramelized.

ingredients: Ground pork, Gelatinized broth, Flour, Ginger, Green onions
cooking_instructions: 1. Make dough and filling. 2. Wrap filling with gelatinized broth in thin dough. 3. Steam dumplings. 4. Serve hot with black vinegar and ginger.

ingredients: Ramen noodles, Pork belly, Soy sauce, Mirin, Eggs, Nori, Bamboo shoots, Green onions
cooking_instructions: 1. Prepare rich pork broth (12+ hours). 2. Cook seasoned pork belly. 3. Soft boil eggs. 4. Cook noodles. 5. Assemble bowl with broth, noodles, meat, eggs, and toppings.

ingredients: Bulgur wheat, Parsley, Mint, Tomatoes, Onion, Lemon juice, Olive oil
cooking_instructions: 1. Soak bulgur. 2. Finely chop herbs and vegetables. 3. Mix all ingredients. 4. Season with lemon juice and olive oil. 5. Chill before serving.

ingredients: Chicken, Scotch bonnet peppers, Allspice, Thyme, Garlic, Ginger, Brown sugar, Soy sauce
cooking_instructions: 1. Blend spices and aromatics for jerk marinade. 2. Marinate chicken for 4+ hours. 3. Grill chicken, basting with marinade. 4. Serve with rice and peas.

ingredients: Salmon fillet, Dill, Salt, Sugar, Peppercorns
cooking_instructions: 1. Mix salt, sugar, and crushed peppercorns. 2. Cover salmon with mixture and fresh dill. 3. Wrap and refrigerate for 2-3 days, turning daily. 4. Rinse and slice thinly to serve.

ingredients: Ground beef, Bread, Milk, Eggs, Onions, Curry powder, Dried fruit, Bay leaves
cooking_instructions: 1. Sauté onions and beef. 2. Add curry and dried fruit. 3. Pour into dish with soaked bread. 4. Top with egg-milk mixture. 5. Bake until set.

ingredients: Cauliflower, Heavy cream, Cheddar cheese, Cream cheese, Bacon, Garlic
cooking_instructions: 1. Steam cauliflower florets. 2. Make cheese sauce with cream, cheeses, and garlic. 3. Combine sauce with cauliflower. 4. Top with bacon and bake until bubbly.

ingredients: Spinach, Feta cheese, Phyllo dough, Onions, Dill, Eggs, Olive oil
cooking_instructions: 1. Sauté spinach and onions. 2. Mix with feta, dill, and eggs. 3. Layer phyllo sheets, brushing with oil. 4. Add filling and fold. 5. Bake until golden.

ingredients: French fries, Cheese curds, Gravy, Chives
cooking_instructions: 1. Prepare crispy french fries. 2. Make rich gravy. 3. Top fries with cheese curds. 4. Pour hot gravy over. 5. Garnish with chives.

ingredients: Rice, Beef, Carrots, Spinach, Bean sprouts, Zucchini, Gochujang, Egg
cooking_instructions: 1. Cook rice. 2. Prepare vegetables separately. 3. Cook beef with soy sauce. 4. Arrange rice, vegetables, and beef in a bowl. 5. Top with fried egg and gochujang.

ingredients: Bananas, Eggs, Almond flour, Cinnamon, Vanilla extract
cooking_instructions: 1. Mash bananas. 2. Mix with eggs, almond flour, cinnamon, and vanilla. 3. Cook spoonfuls on a griddle. 4. Flip when bubbles form. 5. Serve with fresh berries.

ingredients: Chicken, Coconut milk, Lemongrass, Kaffir lime leaves, Galangal, Mushrooms, Fish sauce, Lime juice
cooking_instructions: 1. Simmer coconut milk with lemongrass, lime leaves, and galangal. 2. Add chicken and mushrooms. 3. Season with fish sauce and lime juice. 4. Serve hot.

ingredients: Flour, Water, Salt, Oil for frying, Sugar, Cinnamon, Chocolate (for dipping)
cooking_instructions: 1. Boil water with salt. 2. Add flour to make choux pastry. 3. Pipe into hot oil. 4. Fry until golden. 5. Roll in cinnamon-sugar. 6. Serve with chocolate sauce.

ingredients: Beef tenderloin, Puff pastry, Mushroom duxelles, Prosciutto, Dijon mustard
cooking_instructions: 1. Sear beef. 2. Spread with mustard. 3. Wrap in mushroom duxelles and prosciutto. 4. Encase in puff pastry. 5. Bake until golden and beef is cooked to desired doneness.

ingredients: Sushi rice, Nori sheets, Avocado, Cucumber, Carrots, Rice vinegar, Wasabi, Soy sauce
cooking_instructions: 1. Prepare sushi rice. 2. Lay nori on bamboo mat. 3. Spread rice, add vegetable strips. 4. Roll tightly. 5. Slice and serve with wasabi and soy sauce.

ingredients: Chicken, Carrots, Peas, Onions, Celery, Flour, Chicken broth, Pie crust
cooking_instructions: 1. Cook chicken and vegetables. 2. Make roux, add broth for sauce. 3. Combine with chicken and veggies. 4. Pour into pie crust. 5. Top with second crust. 6. Bake until golden.

ingredients: Shrimp, Grits, Bacon, Cheddar cheese, Garlic, Lemon, Green onions
cooking_instructions: 1. Cook grits with cheese. 2. Sauté bacon. 3. Cook shrimp with garlic and lemon. 4. Serve shrimp over cheesy grits. 5. Garnish with green onions.

ingredients: Basmati rice, Mixed vegetables, Yogurt, Biryani spices, Fried onions, Saffron
cooking_instructions: 1. Parboil rice. 2. Cook vegetables with spices. 3. Layer rice and vegetables. 4. Add saffron milk. 5. Steam until rice is fully cooked. 6. Garnish with fried onions.

ingredients: Lobster, Shrimp stock, Heavy cream, Tomato paste, Brandy, Herbs, Butter
cooking_instructions: 1. Sauté lobster shells. 2. Add brandy and flambé. 3. Add stock and simmer. 4. Strain and add cream. 5. Finish with lobster meat and herbs.

ingredients: Black beans, Pork (various cuts), Beef, Sausage, Orange, Bay leaves, Rice
cooking_instructions: 1. Soak beans overnight. 2. Cook beans with meats and bay leaves. 3. Simmer until meat is tender and beans are creamy. 4. Serve with rice and orange slices.

ingredients: Spinach, Paneer cheese, Onions, Tomatoes, Garam masala, Cream
cooking_instructions: 1. Blanch and puree spinach. 2. Sauté onions and tomatoes. 3. Add spinach and spices. 4. Simmer with paneer cubes. 5. Finish with cream.

ingredients: Various fish, Shellfish, Fennel, Tomatoes, Saffron, Orange zest, Garlic, Herbs
cooking_instructions: 1. Make fish stock. 2. Sauté vegetables. 3. Add stock, saffron, and orange zest. 4. Add fish and shellfish. 5. Simmer briefly. 6. Serve with rouille and bread.

ingredients: Pie crust, Lemon juice, Sugar, Cornstarch, Egg yolks, Egg whites
cooking_instructions: 1. Blind bake pie crust. 2. Cook lemon filling. 3. Pour into crust. 4. Make meringue with egg whites and sugar. 5. Top pie with meringue. 6. Bake until golden.

ingredients: Rice, Black beans, Onions, Bell peppers, Cilantro, Salsa Lizano
cooking_instructions: 1. Cook rice and beans separately. 2. Sauté onions and peppers. 3. Mix rice, beans, and vegetables. 4. Season with Salsa Lizano. 5. Garnish with cilantro.

ingredients: Quinoa, Parsley, Mint, Tomatoes, Cucumber, Lemon juice, Olive oil
cooking_instructions: 1. Cook quinoa and cool. 2. Finely chop herbs and vegetables. 3. Mix all ingredients. 4. Season with lemon juice and olive oil. 5. Chill before serving.

ingredients: Whole turkey, Butter, Herbs, Salt, Pepper, Onions, Celery, Carrots
cooking_instructions: 1. Brine turkey overnight. 2. Stuff with herbs and vegetables. 3. Rub with butter and seasonings. 4. Roast, basting regularly. 5. Rest before carving.

ingredients: Rice, Tomatoes, Onions, Bell peppers, Scotch bonnet peppers, Spices, Vegetable oil
cooking_instructions: 1. Blend tomatoes, onions, and peppers. 2. Fry blended mixture with spices. 3. Add rice and water. 4. Simmer until rice is cooked and absorbs all liquid.

ingredients: Rice noodles, Vegetable broth, Tofu, Bean sprouts, Basil, Lime, Cinnamon, Star anise
cooking_instructions: 1. Simmer broth with spices. 2. Cook rice noodles. 3. Prepare tofu. 4. Assemble bowls with noodles and tofu. 5. Pour hot broth over. 6. Serve with bean sprouts, basil, and lime.

ingredients: Coconut milk, Sugar, Vanilla extract, Salt
cooking_instructions: 1. Mix coconut milk, sugar, vanilla, and salt. 2. Chill mixture. 3. Churn in ice cream maker. 4. Freeze until firm.

ingredients: Chicken breast, Mixed vegetables, Garlic, Ginger, Low-sodium soy sauce, Sesame oil
cooking_instructions: 1. Slice chicken and vegetables. 2. Stir-fry chicken. 3. Add vegetables, garlic, and ginger. 4. Season with low-sodium soy sauce and sesame oil.

ingredients: Flour, Yeast, Salt, Brown sugar, Baking soda, Coarse salt
cooking_instructions: 1. Make dough and let rise. 2. Shape into pretzels. 3. Boil in water with baking soda. 4. Sprinkle with coarse salt. 5. Bake until golden brown.

ingredients: Flour, Honey, Coffee, Oil, Eggs, Cinnamon, Cloves, Allspice
cooking_instructions: 1. Mix wet ingredients. 2. Combine dry ingredients. 3. Mix wet and dry ingredients. 4. Pour into cake pan. 5. Bake until a toothpick comes out clean.

ingredients: Oats, Lentils, Nuts, Vegetables, Vegetable stock, Spices
cooking_instructions: 1. Cook lentils. 2. Sauté vegetables and nuts. 3. Mix with oats and spices. 4. Add stock and simmer. 5. Bake in oven until firm.

ingredients: Watermelon, Feta cheese, Mint, Red onion, Olive oil, Balsamic vinegar
cooking_instructions: 1. Cube watermelon. 2. Thinly slice red onion. 3. Crumble feta. 4. Mix all ingredients. 5. Dress with olive oil and balsamic. 6. Garnish with mint.

ingredients: Flour, Yeast, Sugar, Cinnamon, Butter, Cream cheese, Colored sugar
cooking_instructions: 1. Make sweet dough and let rise. 2. Roll out and fill with cinnamon-sugar. 3. Shape into a ring. 4. Bake until golden. 5. Top with cream cheese frosting and colored sugar.

ingredients: Beets, Cabbage, Potatoes, Carrots, Onions, Vegetable broth, Dill
cooking_instructions: 1. Sauté vegetables. 2. Add broth and simmer until vegetables are tender. 3. Blend half the soup. 4. Combine with unblended half. 5. Serve with fresh dill.

ingredients: Rice noodles, Tofu, Eggs, Bean sprouts, Peanuts, Tamarind paste, Fish sauce, Palm sugar
cooking_instructions: 1. Soak rice noodles. 2. Stir-fry tofu and eggs. 3. Add noodles and sauce. 4. Toss with bean sprouts and peanuts. 5. Serve with lime wedges.

ingredients: Dates, Milk, Banana, Yogurt, Honey, Cinnamon
cooking_instructions: 1. Soak dates in warm milk. 2. Blend dates and milk with other ingredients. 3. Pour into glasses. 4. Sprinkle with cinnamon.

ingredients: Flour, Yeast, Milk, Butter, Eggs, Mixed spices, Dried fruit, Sugar
cooking_instructions: 1. Make dough with fruit and spices. 2. Let rise. 3. Shape into buns. 4. Pipe crosses on top. 5. Bake until golden. 6. Glaze with sugar syrup.

ingredients: Pound cake, Strawberries, Blueberries, Whipped cream, Vanilla pudding
cooking_instructions: 1. Cube pound cake. 2. Layer cake, berries, pudding, and cream in a clear bowl. 3. Repeat layers. 4. Top with whipped cream and arrange berries in flag pattern.

ingredients: Flattened rice, Peanuts, Curry leaves, Mustard seeds, Turmeric, Dried fruits
cooking_instructions: 1. Fry flattened rice until crisp. 2. Fry peanuts and spices. 3. Mix with fried rice. 4. Add dried fruits. 5. Season with salt and sugar.

ingredients: Ground pork, Shrimp, Napa cabbage, Ginger, Garlic, Dumpling wrappers
cooking_instructions: 1. Mix filling ingredients. 2. Place filling in wrappers. 3. Fold and pleat to seal. 4. Steam or pan-fry. 5. Serve with dipping sauce.

ingredients: Avocados, Tomatoes, Onions, Cilantro, Lime juice, Jalapeño
cooking_instructions: 1. Mash avocados. 2. Dice tomatoes, onions, and jalapeño. 3. Mix all ingredients. 4. Season with lime juice and salt. 5. Serve with tortilla chips.

ingredients: Cornmeal, Water, Salt, Canned tomatoes, Onions, Bell peppers, Carrots, Beans, Curry powder
cooking_instructions: 1. Cook cornmeal into a thick porridge (pap). 2. Sauté vegetables for chakalaka. 3. Add tomatoes, beans, and spices. 4. Simmer chakalaka until thickened. 5. Serve pap with chakalaka on top.

ingredients: Rice, Ground beef, Eggs, Gravy, Green onions
cooking_instructions: 1. Cook rice. 2. Form beef into patties and cook. 3. Fry eggs. 4. Make gravy. 5. Assemble: rice, patty, egg, gravy. 6. Garnish with green onions.

ingredients: Chicken, Carrots, Parsnips, Zucchini, Herbs, Low-FODMAP broth
cooking_instructions: 1. Make broth with chicken and allowed vegetables. 2. Shred chicken. 3. Cut vegetables into small pieces. 4. Combine chicken, vegetables, and broth. 5. Simmer until vegetables are tender.

ingredients: Ribeye steak, Butter, Garlic, Rosemary, Salt, Pepper
cooking_instructions: 1. Season steak. 2. Vacuum seal with butter and herbs. 3. Cook in sous vide bath at 129°F for 1-2 hours. 4. Sear in hot pan to finish.

ingredients: Nori sheets, Sushi rice, Avocado, Cucumber, Carrots, Tofu, Vegan mayo, Soy sauce
cooking_instructions: 1. Prepare sushi rice. 2. Lay out large nori sheet. 3. Spread rice and add fillings. 4. Roll tightly like a burrito. 5. Slice in half and serve with soy sauce.

ingredients: Cauliflower, Eggs, Cheese, Almond flour, Tomato sauce, Mozzarella, Basil
cooking_instructions: 1. Rice cauliflower and squeeze out moisture. 2. Mix with eggs, cheese, and almond flour for crust. 3. Bake crust. 4. Top with sauce and cheese. 5. Bake again until cheese melts.

ingredients: Jackfruit, BBQ sauce, Onions, Burger buns, Coleslaw
cooking_instructions: 1. Shred jackfruit. 2. Sauté with onions and BBQ sauce. 3. Simmer until tender. 4. Serve on buns with coleslaw.

ingredients: Eggs, Tomatoes, Bell peppers, Onions, Cumin, Paprika, English muffins, Hollandaise sauce
cooking_instructions: 1. Make shakshuka base. 2. Poach eggs in sauce. 3. Toast English muffins. 4. Assemble: muffin, shakshuka, egg, hollandaise.

ingredients: Oats, Greek yogurt, Protein powder, Chia seeds, Berries, Honey
cooking_instructions: 1. Mix oats, yogurt, protein powder, and chia seeds. 2. Add a little milk if needed. 3. Refrigerate overnight. 4. Top with berries and honey before serving.

ingredients: Fruit juice, Sodium alginate, Calcium lactate, Water
cooking_instructions: 1. Mix juice with sodium alginate. 2. Prepare calcium lactate bath. 3. Drop juice mixture into bath to form caviar. 4. Rinse caviar in clean water.

ingredients: Chicken, Jerk seasoning, Rice, Beans, Plantains, Mango salsa
cooking_instructions: 1. Marinate chicken in jerk seasoning. 2. Grill chicken. 3. Cook rice and beans. 4. Fry plantains. 5. Make mango salsa. 6. Assemble bowl.

ingredients: Pork belly, Daikon, Carrots, Cilantro, Jalapeños, Mayonnaise, Corn tortillas
cooking_instructions: 1. Cook pork belly until crispy. 2. Pickle daikon and carrots. 3. Warm tortillas. 4. Assemble tacos with all ingredients.

ingredients: Beef bones, Rice noodles, Beef slices, Spices, Bean sprouts, Herbs
cooking_instructions: 1. Pressure cook bones and spices for broth. 2. Cook rice noodles. 3. Assemble bowls with noodles and raw beef slices. 4. Pour hot broth over. 5. Serve with herbs and bean sprouts.

ingredients: Lamb, Peanut butter, Tomatoes, Potatoes, Carrots, Onions, Spices
cooking_instructions: 1. Brown lamb. 2. Add vegetables and spices. 3. Stir in peanut butter and tomatoes. 4. Simmer until meat is tender and stew is thick.

ingredients: White fish, Lime juice, Tomatoes, Onions, Cilantro, Avocado, Tostadas
cooking_instructions: 1. Cure fish in lime juice. 2. Mix with chopped vegetables. 3. Serve on tostadas with sliced avocado.

ingredients: Sourdough bread, Cheddar cheese, Kimchi, Butter
cooking_instructions: 1. Butter bread slices. 2. Layer cheese and kimchi between bread. 3. Grill in pan until cheese melts and bread is golden.

ingredients: Black-eyed peas, Palm oil, Plantains, Tomatoes, Onions, Ginger, Chili
cooking_instructions: 1. Cook black-eyed peas. 2. Fry plantains. 3. Make tomato stew with palm oil. 4. Combine peas with stew. 5. Serve with fried plantains.

ingredients: Kangaroo fillet, Quandong (native peach), Red wine, Thyme, Butter
cooking_instructions: 1. Marinate kangaroo in herbs. 2. Grill kangaroo. 3. Make sauce with quandongs and red wine. 4. Serve steak with sauce.

ingredients: Rice, Chicken stock, Ginger, Shredded chicken, Century egg, Green onions
cooking_instructions: 1. Cook rice in excess chicken stock until porridge-like. 2. Add ginger and chicken. 3. Serve topped with sliced century egg and green onions.

ingredients: Lamb, Preserved lemon, Olives, Saffron, Onions, Garlic, Couscous
cooking_instructions: 1. Brown lamb. 2. Add onions, garlic, and spices. 3. Simmer with preserved lemon and olives. 4. Serve over couscous.
